* She looked up at Rion as he tilted towards her a little while flying, 
smiling but thinking that it was juts a detailed saying of what she had 
spoken.*

" Yeah."

* She looked ahead of her for a sec to make sure that she wouldn't run into 
anything or step on any spiders that might jump out.*

" Then we can find people that can halep us find our moms and dads!"

* But Diana stopped and had to muffle a giggle when Rion was suddely blown 
to the ground, not concerned because she knew that he was ok. He was a 
walking pin cucjin, after all.
But she started to walk again as Rion got to his feet and started to walk 
along with her, nudging him with her shoulder and looking at him to let him 
know that she had seen his flying skills and wouldn't get away with showing 
off if he did it.
She wiggled her whiskers at him for a sec when he asked her to use her 
scanners, shrugging.*

" Yeah, I guess I could. But...I'm kinda a beginner."

* Diaia switched on her scanners, finding the program of them after 
searching for a sec.
She hoped that she could just switch them on without searching, but she 
would have to be more grown for that.
It wasn't long before there were a few blips on her screen, but they were 
VERY far away.
Diana sighed.*

" There's lots of signatures...but they're ways away. Like...weeks away. And 
i don't think my comm-link is working. Hay! Let's run a ways. It could be 
just static ghosts."

* Diana then went off at a sprint, her scanners getting fuzzy at every 
step.*
